even need bodies.

717
01:02:35,895 --> 01:02:41,501
Now, um, wh-what would you
say to the possibility...

718
01:02:41,601 --> 01:02:46,339
that because something
happened to you,

719
01:02:46,439 --> 01:02:49,175
uh, something that never does
or isn't supposed to,

720
01:02:49,275 --> 01:02:54,013
that you are, are closer
to that energy level...

721
01:02:54,114 --> 01:02:57,050
than any one body has ever been?

722
01:02:58,284 --> 01:03:00,320
I'd say, "So what?"

723
01:03:04,891 --> 01:03:08,361
So what?

724
01:03:08,461 --> 01:03:12,866
Jeremy, y-you know,
y-your life up 'til now has been...

725
01:03:12,966 --> 01:03:16,203
that farmhouse and, uh,
and the 12 acres of earth.

726
01:03:16,303 --> 01:03:18,205
You know, you've kind
of lived in books.

727
01:03:18,305 --> 01:03:21,708
But I think you're starting
to find out now that the misery...

728
01:03:21,808 --> 01:03:23,910
that you read about is real.

729
01:03:24,011 --> 01:03:26,546
The tragedy is, is real
in all those stories, Jeremy.

730
01:03:26,647 --> 01:03:29,550
Did you think that it wasn't?

731
01:03:29,650 --> 01:03:34,888
I mean, my God, that deer hunt--
You think that's the dark side
of man? Killing for pleasure?

732
01:03:34,988 --> 01:03:39,827
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry,
but you haven't begun to see what we do.

733
01:03:39,927 --> 01:03:44,331
We're-- Jesus, we're stumbling around
in a very dark age...

734
01:03:44,431 --> 01:03:46,767
basically just trying
not to kill each other.

735
01:03:46,867 --> 01:03:50,504
So it hurts me when you say, "So what?"

736
01:03:50,604 --> 01:03:54,608
because you are not
just different, Jeremy.

737
01:03:54,708 --> 01:03:58,345
I think that you have
a mind that, uh,

738
01:03:58,446 --> 01:04:03,017
that we won't evolve to for like, uh,
thousands of years.

739
01:04:03,117 --> 01:04:05,853
You're maybe the man of the future
right here and now.

740
01:04:05,953 --> 01:04:10,157
I don't know.
And I'm-I'm not here to hurt you.

741
01:04:10,258 --> 01:04:14,195
Jeremy, I want
to be a-a-a friend.

742
01:04:14,295 --> 01:04:16,364
[ Sighs ]

743
01:04:16,464 --> 01:04:20,368
I want to talk with you.

744
01:04:20,468 --> 01:04:25,907
Well... I mean,
did you ever have a friend?

745
01:04:28,643 --> 01:04:31,379
I don't need a friend.

746
01:04:32,647 --> 01:04:35,817
Really?

747
01:04:35,917 --> 01:04:38,219
Gee, I thought
you were a genius.

748
01:04:44,092 --> 01:04:47,162
You know what I say is true.

749
01:04:54,469 --> 01:04:58,940
Are you telling me you, like,
never shook anybody's hand before?

750
01:05:08,950 --> 01:05:11,219
Ah, how do you do?

751
01:05:11,320 --> 01:05:15,824
Hmm? Now we've been
properly introduced.

752
01:05:22,297 --> 01:05:24,266
Want to see a trick?

753
01:05:34,476 --> 01:05:37,012
[ Chuckles ]

754
01:05:38,747 --> 01:05:40,849
[ Laughs ]

755
01:05:47,523 --> 01:05:49,959
Hmm.

756
01:05:55,431 --> 01:05:57,333
Wow.

757
01:06:02,438 --> 01:06:05,842
They were afraid
to touch me after a while.

758
01:06:05,942 --> 01:06:08,711
My grandma and grandpa, they--

759
01:06:08,845 --> 01:06:10,980
They got really scared.

760
01:06:11,114 --> 01:06:13,583
What? To touch you?

761
01:06:15,118 --> 01:06:17,020
Jeremy, that's not right.

762
01:06:17,120 --> 01:06:21,324
No way.

763
01:06:23,626 --> 01:06:25,528
That's not right.

764
01:07:16,613 --> 01:07:18,982
[ Shifts Into Park,
Stops Engine ]

765
01:07:31,095 --> 01:07:33,330
[ Knocking ]

766
01:08:05,630 --> 01:08:07,565
Doug.

767
01:08:07,665 --> 01:08:10,168
You've done a little
spring cleaning?

768
01:08:13,471 --> 01:08:15,707
What the hell are you
doing here, Doug?

769
01:08:15,807 --> 01:08:18,209
A couple of my deputies
told me that Harley Duncan...

770
01:08:18,309 --> 01:08:21,713
got rid of every
goddamn gun in his house.

771
01:08:21,813 --> 01:08:25,517
Said he dropped out of
the marksman tourney over in Butte too.

772
01:08:25,617 --> 01:08:29,220
The one he wins every year.

773
01:08:29,320 --> 01:08:33,058
I just ain't huntin'
no more, Doug.

774
01:08:33,158 --> 01:08:35,527
Is that some kind of crime?

775
01:08:37,562 --> 01:08:40,498
I just got lots
of other stuff to do.

776
01:08:40,599 --> 01:08:43,335
You gonna stop
carrying one on the job?

777
01:08:46,104 --> 01:08:49,674
If you can't pick it up and use it,
that's a liability.

778
01:08:56,448 --> 01:08:59,184
I want you to level with me.

779
01:08:59,284 --> 01:09:02,154
I already know you snuck off
hunting with the boys,

780
01:09:02,254 --> 01:09:04,690
which is the last damn thing
you should have done.

781
01:09:04,790 --> 01:09:06,792
Yeah, I know.

782
01:09:06,892 --> 01:09:09,695
I know.

783
01:09:09,795 --> 01:09:11,864
[ Sighs ]

784
01:09:11,964 --> 01:09:16,669
And I popped this pretty doe,
just up at Little Lake.

785
01:09:16,769 --> 01:09:22,207
Let me tell you something, Doug.
You ever tell anybody I said this,
I'm moving out of town.

786
01:09:24,643 --> 01:09:29,215
That... kid?

787
01:09:29,315 --> 01:09:34,053
He lays his hand on the deer
while it's still shakin'...

788
01:09:34,153 --> 01:09:37,823
and then he touches me
at the same time.

789
01:09:37,923 --> 01:09:41,527
Now, I can't figure out why...

790
01:09:41,627 --> 01:09:47,166
'til my heart starts poundin'
and I'm shakin',

791
01:09:47,266 --> 01:09:50,002
and I'm feelin' myself
hurt and scared shitless,

792
01:09:50,102 --> 01:09:53,506
slippin' away in the goddamn dark.

793
01:09:55,942 --> 01:09:58,277
That's the worst thing I ever felt.

794
01:09:58,378 --> 01:10:01,948
It's like I could feel
that animal dyin'.

795
01:10:02,048 --> 01:10:05,985
[ Exhales ] It's like I was
the goddamn thing.

796
01:10:06,085 --> 01:10:09,489
- Aw, come on, Harley.
- Doug, I swear.

797
01:10:09,589 --> 01:10:13,359
Now... I--

798
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:16,696
I just can't do it anymore.

799
01:10:16,796 --> 01:10:20,033
I can't look at something
down the barrel of a gun
without thinking about it.

800
01:10:20,133 --> 01:10:22,369
I've tried it.

801
01:10:22,469 --> 01:10:26,206
I'm telling you,
that thing ain't normal.

802
01:10:26,306 --> 01:10:30,544
I'm telling you, he took whatever was
in that goddamn deer,

803
01:10:30,644 --> 01:10:33,547
and he put it right into me.

804
01:10:37,350 --> 01:10:41,488
[ Door Creaking Open ]

805
01:10:49,930 --> 01:10:51,865
[ Doug ] I'm sorry, son.

806
01:10:51,965 --> 01:10:55,669
Uh... Jessie said...

807
01:10:55,769 --> 01:10:58,105
it may be okay
for you to come with me.

808
01:11:01,542 --> 01:11:05,679
[ Crickets Chirping,
Car Approaching ]

809
01:11:05,779 --> 01:11:09,717
[ Engine Idling ]

810
01:11:09,817 --> 01:11:14,021
[ Turns Off Engine ]

811
01:11:14,121 --> 01:11:17,358
I don't know what it is you do.

812
01:11:17,458 --> 01:11:21,695
I'm not even sure
I believe you can do it.

813
01:11:23,798 --> 01:11:29,036
But if you can,
I need your help.

814
01:11:29,136 --> 01:11:32,373
- [ Owl Hooting ]
- [ Sighs ]

815
01:11:56,431 --> 01:11:59,300
[ Maxine ]
Doug Barnum, don't you do this.

816
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:02,337
- That boy should not be in this house!
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

817
01:12:02,437 --> 01:12:04,506
- Go to bed, Maxine.
- If you heard the stories I've heard,

818
01:12:04,606 --> 01:12:06,674
- you wouldn't want him in this house!
- Go on, go on.

819
01:12:06,775 --> 01:12:08,843
- Go back to bed.
- I'm telling you,
that boy should not be here.

820
01:12:08,943 --> 01:12:10,979
Go to bed, Maxine.

821
01:12:51,587 --> 01:12:53,489
[ Sighs ]

822
01:12:55,257 --> 01:12:59,128
[ Sighs ]

823
01:13:04,266 --> 01:13:07,570
She knows you're here.

824
01:13:16,779 --> 01:13:18,914
[ Doug ]
Talk to me, woman.

825
01:13:19,014 --> 01:13:24,186
Tell me what
I can do for you, Emma.

826
01:13:24,287 --> 01:13:27,056
She can't go,

827
01:13:27,156 --> 01:13:31,861
not until she knows
you're gonna get through this.

828
01:13:31,961 --> 01:13:36,799
She says the both of you.

829
01:13:36,899 --> 01:13:38,835
You and Steven.

830
01:13:42,405 --> 01:13:44,540
Steven?

831
01:13:47,410 --> 01:13:50,046
What the hell do you
want me to do?

832
01:13:50,179 --> 01:13:54,117
What should I do?

833
01:13:54,250 --> 01:13:56,219
Throw my arms around him?

834
01:13:58,421 --> 01:14:03,960
She wants you to remember the snow
when Steven was younger.

835
01:14:05,595 --> 01:14:07,664
And it was snowing.

836
01:14:07,797 --> 01:14:10,300
You were all playing in it.

837
01:14:12,102 --> 01:14:16,873
A snowball fight.
And she lost her--

838
01:14:16,973 --> 01:14:20,544
Ring.
You lost your wedding ring.

839
01:14:20,677 --> 01:14:24,147
You looked down at your hand,
and it was gone.

840
01:14:24,281 --> 01:14:26,383
We all looked.

841
01:14:26,516 --> 01:14:32,356
Me and Steven,
we dug through the snow all afternoon.

842
01:14:32,456 --> 01:14:36,293
He came back
from school every day,

843
01:14:36,393 --> 01:14:39,630
digging through the snowbanks,
thinking he'd find it.

844
01:14:39,763 --> 01:14:44,768
She cried that you both
loved her so much.

845
01:14:44,902 --> 01:14:47,938
The way each of you
looked so hard for it.

846
01:14:48,072 --> 01:14:51,442
[ Sighs ]
I remember that.

847
01:14:51,575 --> 01:14:53,544
I do.

848
01:14:54,912 --> 01:14:57,348
The silver box.

849
01:14:57,448 --> 01:15:00,117
The silver box on the table.

850
01:15:05,456 --> 01:15:08,993
Oh, no, Mama. No.

851
01:15:16,467 --> 01:15:19,170
[ Gasps, Sobs ]
Oh, no.

852
01:15:24,275 --> 01:15:26,144
[ Sobs ]

853
01:15:26,277 --> 01:15:28,646
[ Jeremy ]
He found it at the old house...

854
01:15:28,780 --> 01:15:31,749
in a garden he was tilling.

855
01:15:31,883 --> 01:15:34,719
He said he knew right away
what it was...

856
01:15:36,521 --> 01:15:40,692
- and that it was time to come home.
- [ Inhales Deeply ]

857
01:15:42,026 --> 01:15:46,197
She says she believes
in miracles now...

858
01:15:46,297 --> 01:15:48,500
and that you should too.

859
01:15:50,869 --> 01:15:53,938
[ Sighs ]

860
01:15:55,140 --> 01:15:58,610
She thinks I'm an angel...

861
01:16:01,212 --> 01:16:03,348
come to take her home.

862
01:16:05,217 --> 01:16:09,888
And to bring you and Steven
together again.

863
01:16:12,390 --> 01:16:15,894
Remind you how much you're still
in each other's hearts.

864
01:16:15,994 --> 01:16:18,130
[ Sighs ]

865
01:16:18,230 --> 01:16:21,400
Everything about each other
we don't like.

866
01:16:21,500 --> 01:16:23,468
You know that.

867
01:16:25,771 --> 01:16:29,474
He loves you more than
any man in the whole world.

868
01:16:29,575 --> 01:16:34,513
And she won't go,
she won't leave this place,

869
01:16:34,613 --> 01:16:39,084
this room or this world...

870
01:16:39,184 --> 01:16:44,556
until you know
that you still have a son.

871
01:16:49,361 --> 01:16:52,097
She'd like to feel
the ring on her finger.

872
01:16:52,198 --> 01:16:55,935
[ Sighs ]

873
01:16:57,169 --> 01:17:01,907
[ Doug Gasping ]

874
01:17:06,379 --> 01:17:08,781
[ Sighing ]

875
01:17:19,859 --> 01:17:23,196
You can hear.

876
01:17:23,296 --> 01:17:27,233
[ Sniffling ]

877
01:17:27,333 --> 01:17:31,304
Oh, it's all right.

878
01:17:31,404 --> 01:17:33,473
[ Crying ]
Angel, it's all right.

879
01:17:35,909 --> 01:17:39,646
[ Sighs ]

880
01:17:41,748 --> 01:17:45,151
Good-bye, Emma, sweetie.

881
01:18:01,501 --> 01:18:03,537
[ Car Approaching ]

882
01:18:14,114 --> 01:18:16,016
- Hurry!
- What?

883
01:18:16,116 --> 01:18:18,018
- He's got him up there right now!
- What? What is--

884
01:18:18,118 --> 01:18:20,053
He's got him up there
with your mama!

885
01:18:23,790 --> 01:18:26,360
[ Panting ]

886
01:18:26,460 --> 01:18:28,395
Poppa.

887
01:19:07,935 --> 01:19:09,937
[ Crying ]

888
01:19:16,444 --> 01:19:21,049
[ Continues Crying ]

889
01:19:54,082 --> 01:19:59,421
[ Crowd Chattering ]

890
01:19:59,521 --> 01:20:03,392
[ Chattering Continues ]

891
01:20:03,492 --> 01:20:08,730
[ Chattering Continues ]

892
01:20:15,604 --> 01:20:17,606
Why don't we just
tell them all to stop,

893
01:20:17,706 --> 01:20:20,209
and they can just
take a picture or something.

894
01:20:22,277 --> 01:20:25,514
Jeremy, are you okay?

895
01:20:25,614 --> 01:20:27,616
They're wondering if I killed her.

896
01:20:30,286 --> 01:20:33,055
Don't tell me you're
seeing inside them again.

897
01:20:46,402 --> 01:20:49,505
What are people like
on the inside?

898
01:20:54,577 --> 01:20:58,981
Inside most people there's
a feeling of being separate.

899
01:20:59,081 --> 01:21:01,818
Separated from everything.

900
01:21:01,918 --> 01:21:05,655
And?

901
01:21:05,755 --> 01:21:08,157
And they're not.

902
01:21:08,257 --> 01:21:12,328
They're part of absolutely
everyone and everything.

903
01:21:12,428 --> 01:21:17,500
Everything?
I'm part of this tree?

904
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:20,170
Part of Zack barking over fences?

905
01:21:20,270 --> 01:21:24,340
You're telling me that I'm part
of some fisherman in Italy...

906
01:21:24,441 --> 01:21:26,810
on some ocean
I've never even heard of?

907
01:21:26,910 --> 01:21:29,345
There's some guy
sitting on death row.

908
01:21:29,446 --> 01:21:32,315
- I'm part of him too?
- You don't believe me.

909
01:21:32,415 --> 01:21:36,286
It's hard to believe that,
all of that.

910
01:21:36,386 --> 01:21:41,925
Well, that's because you have this spot
that you can't see past.

911
01:21:42,058 --> 01:21:45,095
My grams and gramps had it.

912
01:21:45,228 --> 01:21:49,366
A spot where they were taught
they were disconnected from everything.

913
01:21:49,466 --> 01:21:53,303
So that's what they'd see
if they could?

914
01:21:53,403 --> 01:21:55,439
That they're connected?

915
01:21:58,408 --> 01:22:00,377
And how beautiful
they really are.

916
01:22:02,246 --> 01:22:07,284
- [ Inhales Deeply ]
- And that there's
no need to hide or lie.

917
01:22:07,417 --> 01:22:09,820
And that it's possible...

918
01:22:09,920 --> 01:22:13,357
to talk to someone
without any lies.

919
01:22:13,457 --> 01:22:16,126
With no sarcasms,

920
01:22:16,260 --> 01:22:20,497
no deceptions,
no exaggerations...

921
01:22:20,598 --> 01:22:25,002
or any of the things
that people use to confuse the truth.

922
01:22:25,102 --> 01:22:29,039
I don't know a single person
who does that.

923
01:22:29,173 --> 01:22:31,776
Hold out your hand.

924
01:22:35,012 --> 01:22:38,949
Put your fingers up.

925
01:23:00,238 --> 01:23:03,441
Wow.

926
01:23:03,574 --> 01:23:05,610
Is that your heartbeat?

927
01:23:05,743 --> 01:23:08,613
And yours.

928
01:23:12,417 --> 01:23:15,520
Wow, this feels strange.

929
01:23:17,422 --> 01:23:20,258
You're afraid someone
will see us holding hands.

930
01:23:22,427 --> 01:23:24,763
You're really nervous
talking to me.

931
01:23:26,765 --> 01:23:29,034
You don't think
you're pretty enough.

932
01:23:31,436 --> 01:23:33,305
You feel alone.

933
01:23:33,438 --> 01:23:35,340
You feel so alone.

934
01:23:37,375 --> 01:23:42,080
Sometimes you just want
to break out of yourself.

935
01:23:42,180 --> 01:23:45,417
Your father.

936
01:23:45,517 --> 01:23:50,322
Your father hurt you
a long time ago.

937
01:23:52,691 --> 01:23:54,760
You're so sad.

938
01:23:54,860 --> 01:23:58,096
He made you so sad.

939
01:23:58,197 --> 01:24:01,600
He thought you were,
you were ugly and...

940
01:24:01,700 --> 01:24:04,169
and he kept saying you,
you weren't--

941
01:24:04,269 --> 01:24:06,939
- [ Sighs ]
- I'm so sorry.

942
01:24:07,039 --> 01:24:09,608
Do you?

943
01:24:09,708 --> 01:24:12,945
- Do you?
- Do I what?

944
01:24:13,045 --> 01:24:17,049
Do you think I'm ugly?

945
01:24:20,719 --> 01:24:26,292
I don't know what I think
when I look at you.

946
01:24:26,392 --> 01:24:29,462
But sometimes I-I think...

947
01:24:29,562 --> 01:24:33,466
I think you're the most
beautiful face I've ever seen.

948
01:24:53,119 --> 01:24:55,622
What?

949
01:25:07,033 --> 01:25:10,770
What in the name of God
do you think you're doing?

950
01:25:14,441 --> 01:25:16,543
[ Sighs ]

951
01:25:16,643 --> 01:25:19,980
You having a good time
with my daughter?

952
01:25:20,080 --> 01:25:22,682
Wonderful.

953
01:25:22,782 --> 01:25:25,018
It's a good school,
and I feel good--

954
01:25:25,118 --> 01:25:27,687
You think this is funny?

955
01:25:30,490 --> 01:25:31,858
- Funny man, huh?
- Dad!

956
01:25:33,994 --> 01:25:36,697
- You think this is funny,
huh, lover boy?
- Would you stop?

957
01:25:36,797 --> 01:25:38,665
[ Crowd Chattering ]

958
01:25:38,765 --> 01:25:41,168
- Now, I asked you a question,
and I want an answer.
- Would you please let him--

959
01:25:41,268 --> 01:25:43,270
[ Children Screaming ]

960
01:25:43,370 --> 01:25:45,405
- You think it's funny?
- Dad, he wasn't doing anything!

961
01:25:45,505 --> 01:25:47,441
- [ Dad ] Answer me!
- Mr. Kelloway!

962
01:25:47,541 --> 01:25:50,410
[ Jessie ] Let him go.

963
01:25:50,511 --> 01:25:55,416
I said, "Let him go." Dick Kelloway,
you take your hands off him now!

964
01:25:55,516 --> 01:26:01,255
- I thought your boys had rules
about fraternizing.
- I said now.

965
01:26:01,355 --> 01:26:04,592
Keep your state trash
away from my daughter.

966
01:26:06,694 --> 01:26:09,763
Christ, you know nothing happened!

967
01:26:09,864 --> 01:26:13,367
Is that your expert opinion?

968
01:26:14,969 --> 01:26:18,439
You keep that thing on a leash
or I'll slap a lawsuit...

969
01:26:18,539 --> 01:26:23,444
on that state zoo that will shut it down
so fast it will make your head spin.

970
01:26:30,218 --> 01:26:33,154
I am so sorry.

971
01:26:37,391 --> 01:26:39,994
Powder.

972
01:26:58,313 --> 01:27:00,548
[ Sighs ]

973
01:27:46,228 --> 01:27:50,132
[ Voices Echoing From Gym ]

974
01:27:52,735 --> 01:27:57,973
[ Boys Hooting, Sneakers Squeaking ]

975
01:27:58,073 --> 01:28:00,976
[ Laughing ]

976
01:28:02,578 --> 01:28:06,649
[ Hooting Continues,
Basketball Bouncing ]

977
01:28:06,749 --> 01:28:12,321
[ Sneakers Squeaking, Shouting ]

978
01:28:12,421 --> 01:28:17,994
[ Chattering ]

979
01:28:18,094 --> 01:28:21,731
[ Hooting, Chattering ]

980
01:28:23,432 --> 01:28:26,502
- Oh!
- Too bad.

981
01:28:26,602 --> 01:28:29,338
[ Chattering ]

982
01:28:30,606 --> 01:28:33,409
- Oh!
- Oh! Too bad it's mine!

983
01:28:33,509 --> 01:28:35,411
Watch your pick!
Watch your pick!

984
01:28:35,511 --> 01:28:37,547
Run it! Run it!
Run it!

985
01:28:37,647 --> 01:28:40,183
[ Boys Laughing, Door Slams ]

986
01:28:40,283 --> 01:28:42,185
[ Laughing Continues ]

987
01:28:42,285 --> 01:28:46,623
[ Boys Chattering ]

988
01:28:46,723 --> 01:28:51,060
[ Chattering, Laughing Continues ]

989
01:28:51,161 --> 01:28:53,797
[ Laughing ]
Air ball!

990
01:28:53,897 --> 01:28:57,634
[ Sneakers Squeaking, Ball Bouncing ]

991
01:28:57,734 --> 01:29:00,270
[ Hooting, Water Fountain Running ]

992
01:29:15,585 --> 01:29:19,222
Why don't you
take a picture, man?

993
01:29:19,323 --> 01:29:21,224
Hey, Skye!

994
01:29:28,665 --> 01:29:30,567
[ Panting ]

995
01:29:30,667 --> 01:29:33,137
Does this look
like a genius to you?

996
01:29:34,605 --> 01:29:36,807
Peeping Tom faggot, maybe.

997
01:29:36,907 --> 01:29:41,011
You were gettin' an eyeful of him,
weren't you, light bulb?

998
01:29:43,380 --> 01:29:45,482
You want to see what
a real man looks like?

999
01:29:45,582 --> 01:29:47,585
Huh?

1000
01:29:53,357 --> 01:29:58,929
You think you can take me,
freak show, go for it.

1001
01:29:59,063 --> 01:30:02,299
In the meantime...

1002
01:30:02,400 --> 01:30:05,603
I keep the hat.

1003
01:30:05,703 --> 01:30:08,806
When you think you're man enough
to get it back, you take your best shot.

1004
01:30:12,076 --> 01:30:14,445
You think you're
man enough to get it back?

1005
01:30:14,545 --> 01:30:17,615
You take your best shot, tough stuff.

1006
01:30:19,250 --> 01:30:21,219
What did you say?

1007
01:30:21,319 --> 01:30:26,224
I'd beat you to shit
before you got this old hat back.

1008
01:30:28,426 --> 01:30:32,463
That's what he said to you
when he was drunk.

1009
01:30:32,597 --> 01:30:37,268
You were 12 years old,
and he took your father's hat.

1010
01:30:39,204 --> 01:30:41,940
It's the only thing your
real father ever left behind.

1011
01:30:49,047 --> 01:30:51,049
Your stepdad, John.

1012
01:30:51,182 --> 01:30:55,620
That's what he said to you.

1013
01:30:55,720 --> 01:30:58,456
"You think you're man enough
to get it back?

1014
01:30:58,590 --> 01:31:03,028
Then take your best shot,
tough stuff."

1015
01:31:03,128 --> 01:31:07,232
And then he beat you bloody
that night when you tried.

1016
01:31:08,400 --> 01:31:10,302
Hey, fuck you!

1017
01:31:11,903 --> 01:31:16,408
You had marks so dark,
you were embarrassed to suit up for gym.

1018
01:31:17,809 --> 01:31:21,613
I ought to kill you
right now, man.

1019
01:31:21,747 --> 01:31:26,452
I ought to slit your throat and
spit down it while I'm doing it.

1020
01:31:26,585 --> 01:31:30,989
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1021
01:31:31,090 --> 01:31:33,959
Well, what do you know.

1022
01:31:34,093 --> 01:31:36,562
Boogeyman's afraid of lightning.

1023
01:31:36,795 --> 01:31:38,497
Come on!

1024
01:31:47,373 --> 01:31:50,342
- What's the matter, freak show?
- Leave him alone, Johnny! Jesus Christ!

1025
01:31:50,476 --> 01:31:53,245
- He's scared to death!
- Bullshit, Mitch!

1026
01:31:53,379 --> 01:31:56,749
He got a free show.
Now we get one.

1027
01:31:58,985 --> 01:32:04,123
[ Laughing ]
Now that is white!

1028
01:32:09,362 --> 01:32:11,364
Look at that.

1029
01:32:14,033 --> 01:32:16,035
You're as bald as a baby.

1030
01:32:18,338 --> 01:32:20,506
[ John ] He needs some color.

1031
01:32:20,607 --> 01:32:23,276
Doesn't he need some color?

1032
01:32:23,376 --> 01:32:25,445
You definitely need
some color, buddy.

1033
01:32:28,715 --> 01:32:31,618
- [ Gasping ]
- [ John ] Go get him.

1034
01:32:31,718 --> 01:32:33,486
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1035
01:32:33,586 --> 01:32:35,622
Do it!

1036
01:32:48,835 --> 01:32:52,772
- Now you got some color.
- That's enough, John.

1037
01:32:52,873 --> 01:32:55,475
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1038
01:32:55,575 --> 01:32:59,079
[ Sighs, Chuckles ]

1039
01:32:59,179 --> 01:33:02,516
There's not much fight in you,
is there, freak show?

1040
01:33:02,616 --> 01:33:06,420
[ Thunder Clapping ]

1041
01:33:10,691 --> 01:33:14,595
You really think
you can be like us?

1042
01:33:14,695 --> 01:33:17,498
Is that what you think, freak show?

1043
01:33:18,599 --> 01:33:21,435
Hey.

1044
01:33:21,535 --> 01:33:23,470
Hey, what the hell--

1045
01:33:23,570 --> 01:33:25,506
[ Laughing ]

1046
01:33:25,606 --> 01:33:27,775
[ Laughing ]
Holy shit.

1047
01:33:31,212 --> 01:33:34,181
[ Zane ] Look at this.
Look. What's going on here?

1048
01:33:34,281 --> 01:33:37,218
[ Boys Chuckling ]

1049
01:33:37,318 --> 01:33:41,555
- Ah. Ah! Ow! Ow!
- [ John Chuckling ]

1050
01:33:41,655 --> 01:33:43,290
- [ Skye ] What's going on?
- Oh!

1051
01:33:43,391 --> 01:33:45,626
- What's go-- What's going on?
- What the--

1052
01:33:45,726 --> 01:33:49,096
[ Screaming ]

1053
01:34:01,008 --> 01:34:02,910
[ Gasps ]

1054
01:34:38,647 --> 01:34:43,051
Jesus!
His heart stopped beating!

1055
01:34:47,489 --> 01:34:50,225
- You son of a bitch!
- Zane! No, no, no, no!

1056
01:34:50,325 --> 01:34:52,561
- Don't touch him, man!
- What the hell are you?

1057
01:34:52,661 --> 01:34:55,564
- Don't touch him!
- [ Mitch ] Come on, you assholes!

1058
01:34:55,664 --> 01:34:58,734
Go and get some help now!

1059
01:34:58,834 --> 01:35:01,069
Do it!

1060
01:35:02,738 --> 01:35:04,640
Hey, what the hell do you
think you're doing?

1061
01:35:10,746 --> 01:35:12,915
- You got to be kidding me.
- Come on!

1062
01:35:13,015 --> 01:35:15,150
- Just get away from him, man!
- [ Electricity Jolts ]

1063
01:35:22,658 --> 01:35:25,928
Stop it, man!
Come on!

1064
01:35:26,028 --> 01:35:27,997
He's gone!

1065
01:35:35,371 --> 01:35:39,408
[ Coughing ]

1066
01:35:40,910 --> 01:35:43,212
Go get help, you idiots!
Do it!

1067
01:35:43,312 --> 01:35:45,314
- [ Coughing Continues ]
- Now!

1068
01:35:45,414 --> 01:35:48,351
[ Gasping ]

1069
01:35:48,451 --> 01:35:50,620
Come on, man!
You gotta get outta here!

1070
01:35:50,720 --> 01:35:54,757
[ Continues Gasping ]

1071
01:35:54,857 --> 01:35:58,761
- Let him go, John!
- [ Continues Gasping ]

1072
01:35:58,861 --> 01:36:03,166
Listen! Listen!
I can get you out of here!

1073
01:36:03,266 --> 01:36:06,102
I-I've done it before!

1074
01:36:11,875 --> 01:36:17,547
[ Radio Signal Distorting, Static ]

1075
01:36:17,647 --> 01:36:22,419
[ Continues Distorting ]

1076
01:36:22,519 --> 01:36:25,588
[ Distortion, Static Continue ]

1077
01:36:37,801 --> 01:36:40,704
[ Birds Chirping ]

1078
01:36:44,141 --> 01:36:47,878
[ Chirping Continues ]

1079
01:36:59,990 --> 01:37:04,561
[ Unhooks Latch, Gate Creaks ]

1080
01:37:11,335 --> 01:37:14,738
[ Chirping Continues ]

1081
01:38:28,246 --> 01:38:31,650
[ Turns Off Engine,
Sets Parking Brake ]

1082
01:38:31,750 --> 01:38:34,653
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1083
01:38:40,025 --> 01:38:42,094
[ Rumbling Continues ]

1084
01:38:42,227 --> 01:38:44,229
Jeremy?

1085
01:38:55,374 --> 01:38:57,409
Oh.

1086
01:39:02,214 --> 01:39:04,884
They took everything?

1087
01:39:06,218 --> 01:39:09,755
Jeremy, listen to me.
We can track it all down.

1088
01:39:09,889 --> 01:39:12,258
We-We'll find every book.
Uh--

1089
01:39:16,695 --> 01:39:20,599
Why don't you look at me
and say something?

1090
01:39:20,700 --> 01:39:22,868
[ Sighs ]

1091
01:39:26,339 --> 01:39:29,876
Jeremy, listen.

1092
01:39:30,009 --> 01:39:34,247
From the first moment
I saw you down here,

1093
01:39:34,380 --> 01:39:38,951
scared in the dark,
I had this feeling that...

1094
01:39:39,085 --> 01:39:42,955
that you would change
everything I knew.

1095
01:39:43,089 --> 01:39:45,858
And maybe...

1096
01:39:45,992 --> 01:39:50,530
this is not the right place
for someone as beautiful as you.

1097
01:39:50,663 --> 01:39:53,366
But if you come with me...

1098
01:39:53,500 --> 01:39:56,669
I promise you
we'll find a place that is.

1099
01:40:00,507 --> 01:40:02,876
[ Sighs ]

1100
01:40:16,089 --> 01:40:20,227
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

1101
01:40:22,162 --> 01:40:25,399
[ Footsteps Continue ]

1102
01:40:28,001 --> 01:40:29,903
Let's go.

1103
01:40:48,122 --> 01:40:53,727
- [ Car Door Closes, Thunder Rumbling ]
- [ Sighs ]

1104
01:41:02,970 --> 01:41:04,939
Donald.

1105
01:41:13,147 --> 01:41:16,217
Just let him come on down,
Miss Caldwell.

1106
01:41:16,317 --> 01:41:19,086
We don't want no trouble from you.

1107
01:41:19,186 --> 01:41:21,689
What the hell you doin', Jess?

1108
01:41:21,789 --> 01:41:24,225
The right thing.

1109
01:41:25,993 --> 01:41:27,895
[ Sighs ]

1110
01:41:27,995 --> 01:41:31,232
And if you don't see that,

1111
01:41:31,332 --> 01:41:35,336
then why don't you just turn
your head and please, please...

1112
01:41:35,436 --> 01:41:38,339
just look the other way.

1113
01:41:38,439 --> 01:41:42,343
- I don't know how to do that, Jess.
- Of course you do, Doug.

1114
01:41:42,443 --> 01:41:45,346
Christ's sake, just, uh,
you know, turn your head.

1115
01:41:45,446 --> 01:41:47,348
Just like that.

1116
01:41:48,616 --> 01:41:54,356
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1117
01:41:54,456 --> 01:41:58,927
[ Rumbling Continues ]

1118
01:41:59,027 --> 01:42:01,529
[ Ripley ]
Let's do it.

1119
01:42:01,630 --> 01:42:04,699
He can't be out in this weather.

1120
01:42:06,801 --> 01:42:08,837
Where the hell are you
gonna take him?

1121
01:42:14,342 --> 01:42:19,715
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1122
01:42:24,987 --> 01:42:28,657
Let's have a talk.
Come here. Come on.

1123
01:42:34,496 --> 01:42:37,332
Why don't you hit the road, Harley?

1124
01:42:38,934 --> 01:42:43,005
- Do what?
- I said get the hell out of here.

1125
01:42:43,105 --> 01:42:46,342
I'm not gonna
let this happen, Doug.

1126
01:42:46,442 --> 01:42:48,677
You're breakin'
the goddamn law.

1127
01:42:48,777 --> 01:42:51,213
- Lucy, this is Harley--
- I said go away.

1128
01:42:52,781 --> 01:42:55,918
- [ Lucy ] Go ahead, Harley.
- [ Radio Shatters ]

1129
01:42:56,018 --> 01:42:59,188
You're out of your goddamn,
motherfrickin' minds, you know that?

1130
01:42:59,288 --> 01:43:02,191
- All of ya!
- [ Thunder Rumbles ]

1131
01:43:02,291 --> 01:43:07,063
[ Rumbling Continues ]

1132
01:43:10,399 --> 01:43:13,970
Lucy.
Lucy, this is Harley.

1133
01:43:14,070 --> 01:43:17,373
I need some help out here
at the Reed place.

1134
01:43:17,473 --> 01:43:20,042
- A couple of units would be good.
- [ Thunder Rumbling ]

1135
01:43:20,143 --> 01:43:23,546
Jeremy? Powder? Hey!

1136
01:43:23,646 --> 01:43:26,282
[ Doug ] If you're gonna go,
you better go now.

1137
01:43:26,382 --> 01:43:28,351
Jeremy?

1138
01:43:32,155 --> 01:43:34,224
She didn't go someplace.

1139
01:43:35,925 --> 01:43:39,028
- Your wife.
- What?

1140
01:43:39,129 --> 01:43:42,832
I felt her go.

1141
01:43:42,932 --> 01:43:44,868
Not away.

1142
01:43:44,968 --> 01:43:47,003
Just out.

1143
01:43:47,103 --> 01:43:49,673
Everywhere.

1144
01:43:49,773 --> 01:43:52,976
[ Chuckles ]

1145
01:43:53,076 --> 01:43:55,545
"It's become appallingly clear...

1146
01:43:55,645 --> 01:43:59,049
that our technology
has surpassed our humanity."

1147
01:43:59,149 --> 01:44:02,085
Albert Einstein.

1148
01:44:03,453 --> 01:44:07,190
I look at you and l,
I think that someday...

1149
01:44:07,290 --> 01:44:12,729
our humanity might actually
surpass our technology.

1150
01:44:28,479 --> 01:44:34,051
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1151
01:44:34,151 --> 01:44:39,823
[ Rumbling Continues ]

1152
01:44:45,463 --> 01:44:46,597
[ Sighs ]

1153
01:44:48,199 --> 01:44:50,501
Hey! God!

1154
01:44:54,939 --> 01:44:56,941
[ Jessie ] Powder!

1155
01:45:02,780 --> 01:45:05,983
[ Thunder Crashes ]

1156
01:45:06,117 --> 01:45:08,486
[ Rumbling ]

1157
01:45:08,553 --> 01:45:12,690
[ Jessie ] Powder!

1158
01:45:15,093 --> 01:45:17,028
[ Thunder Crashes ]

1159
01:45:22,400 --> 01:45:25,003
- Oh!
- Oh!
- [ Gasps ]
